FBIS4-66900 "jptac005__l94015" JPRS-TAC-94-005-L JPRS Arms Control 6 May 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA Missiles Detargetted by 30 May Missiles Detargetted by 30 May LD0605082394 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0630 GMT 6 May 94 LD0605082394 Moscow 2x2 Television Russian BFN [Text] On 30 May, Russian strategic missiles with nuclear warheads will no longer be aimed at targets located on the territory of the United States and Great Britain. This was announced by Colonel-General Igor Sergeyev, commander in chief of the Strategic Rocket Troops. According to him, the missiles will not be aimed at any target in the world.
